ADR-0074 nothing-to-do short-circuit for architect disposition

Implement three-clause guard that short-circuits architect on empty-diff
re-dispatches: zero commits ahead, validator passed, author accepted.
Eliminates wasted Claude calls and amend-cap budget burn per ADR-0029.

- _short_circuit_nothing_to_do(ctx) checks: git count==0, validator==pass,
  author==accept-as-is signal
- Returns synthetic envelope with short_circuit_reason field for telemetry
- Graceful fallback on git failure; architect runs normally

Tests cover positive and negative cases for all three clauses.

